I"p<p>Just like <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/similar-embodiment-predicts-manifold-alignment">a similar physical environment predicts manifold alignment</a>, so does similar cultural embedding. By being constantly exposed to <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/explicit-position-cues-describe-conceptual-structure">similar metaphors</a>, people naturally internalize <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/world-models-reflect-ideological-structures">similar conceptual structures</a>, and in turn derive <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/manifolds-formalize-emergence">similar neural manifolds</a>, by virtue of being <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/brains-code-relative-object-positions">aligned</a> to the <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/physical-and-conceptual-spaces-are-coded-in-the-same-region">same thing</a>.</p>
